<h2><strong>How Much Do NYSC Members Collect Every Month</strong></h2>
<p>This is a very complex question and it does not have a clear answer. Apart from the federal allowance of N19,800, many corp members may get other forms of payment from their place of primary assignment &#8211; depending on their course of study, ppa and location.</p><div class="lPPjOBRy" style="clear:both;float:left;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-9755093768544960"
     crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
<!-- 12 -->
<ins class="adsbygoogle"
     style="display:block"
     data-ad-client="ca-pub-9755093768544960"
     data-ad-slot="3429136867"
     data-ad-format="auto"
     data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
<script>
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>
<h3><strong>Pay Per Course of Study</strong></h3>
<p>For instance, a corp member who is a medical doctor in a teaching hospital may receive nothing less than N150-200 per month along with the N19,800 Federal Allowance.</p><div class="LWqhaDgO" style="clear:both;float:left;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-9755093768544960"
     crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
